main event: A civilian reported observing an unusual object in the sky over Poulsbo, Washington in January 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 8-10 minutes,The object was described as around 75 to 100 feet in diameter and of a dark color,There were bright lights observed that sometimes appeared to move and sometimes remained stationary,The observer reported no sound associated with the object,The incident involved multiple witnesses, but their statements could not be verified.
sighted object: an unusual object in the sky with bright lights
witness description: A civilian observer who reported seeing the object from their home.
